The paper discusses software development practices and quality assurance activities in the context of a time-constrained event, which suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of iterative brainstorming and agile development practices also suggests a potential fit with the graphics (cs.GR) and cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-categories. Finally, the discussion of communication and planning aligns with the systems and control (cs.SI) sub-category.
